The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 October is 3,652 (422.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 September, there were 210 new confirmed cases (24.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 124 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 69% (86 extra cases).
